oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: A view of the retard structure No. 5 from the north end of a dam on the Thompson's Creek Watershed District. First Public Law 566 floodwater retarding structure completed in the State, located in the Henry County SCD.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: The first Public Law 566 floodwater retarding structure in Tennessee, Site No. 5, was contracted for construction 2.02.1959. Completion date, 8.20.1959. Tennessee's first.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: W. E. Westbrook, SCS
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: RG 82: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Lakes & ponds; Dams; Conservation of natural resources
